headline: Veralto's Earnings Impress, But Guidance Tempers Sentiment
summary: VLTO beat Q4 earnings and lifted margins, but cautious 2026 guidance slowed optimism, sending shares down about 6% after results.

headline: Veralto price target lowered to $102 from $111 at RBC Capital
summary: RBC Capital analyst Deane Dray lowered the firm’s price target on Veralto (VLTO) to $102 from $111 and keeps a Sector Perform rating on the shares. The company reported a modest 1% operating beat and set 2026 guidance capturing consensus at the high-end, or about 1% below at the midpoint, the analyst tells investors in a research note. Veralto remains a high-quality compounder, though the stock is currently out of favor in the prevailing environment, RBC added.Claim 50% Off TipRanks PremiumUnloc
